title: H.S. Football: Parsippany’s Red Hawks stung by Hornets
text:
H.S. Football: Parsippany’s Red Hawks stung by Hornets October 14, 2015 Last updated: Wednesday, October 14, 2015, 12:31 AM Parsippany Life Buy this photo Photos by Jerry Dalia 
Parsippany High School varsity football hosted Hanover Park on Oct. 3. The Red Hawks battled through the rain but couldn’t quite match up against the Hornets, who won the game 43-0. Here, Parsippany’s Nick Bucciarelli makes his move. 
Below, running back Robert Hockey looks for room to turn up field. Parsippany’s next home game will be on Friday, Oct. 30, at 7 p.m. against Morris Catholic. © 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
